<%= faq_schema([
  { question: "How many credits typically transfer between colleges?", answer: "Transfer rates vary widely. Between community colleges and in-state public universities with articulation agreements, 80-100% of credits often transfer. Between unrelated four-year institutions, expect 50-75% of credits to transfer. Credits are more likely to transfer if the courses have equivalent offerings at the receiving institution." },
  { question: "What determines if a credit will transfer?", answer: "The receiving institution evaluates each course for equivalency with their own curriculum. Factors include course content, credit hours, grade earned (typically C or higher), accreditation of the sending institution, and whether the course fulfills a requirement in your new degree program. General education courses transfer most reliably." },
  { question: "Do AP and CLEP credits transfer?", answer: "Most colleges accept AP credits for scores of 3 or higher, though selective institutions may require 4 or 5. CLEP credits are accepted by about 2,900 colleges. However, transfer policies vary by institution, and some departments may not accept standardized exam credits for major-specific courses." },
  { question: "How can I maximize credit transfer?", answer: "Research the receiving institution's transfer credit policies before enrolling. Use articulation agreements and transfer guides. Take courses that have clear equivalents at your target school. Maintain a GPA above the minimum transfer threshold. Keep all syllabi and course descriptions as they may be needed for course-by-course evaluation." },
  { question: "What happens to credits that do not transfer?", answer: "Non-transferable credits may still appear on your transcript as elective credit, which counts toward total credit hours but may not fulfill specific degree requirements. In the worst case, you may need to retake equivalent courses at the new institution, adding time and cost to your degree." }
]) %>

<%= calculator_schema_with_ratings(
  name: "Credit Transfer Calculator",
  description: "Calculate transferable college credits, remaining requirements, estimated time to graduation, and cost savings when transferring schools.",
  url: education_credit_transfer_url,
  category: "EducationalApplication",
  calculator_slug: "credit-transfer"
) %>

